rules: Rule1: Either Dr. Smith is available as a veterinarian or Dr. Jones is available as a veterinarian.

Rule2: If Dr. Jones is available as a veterinarian, then whenever it is not true that the dog showing symptoms of parvovirus implies parvovirus is diagnosed in the dog, the dog does not require medication.

Rule3: Under the condition that the dog has a scheduled appointment in the morning, if Dr. Smith is available as a veterinarian, then provided that it is false that the dog shows symptoms of parvovirus only if parvovirus is diagnosed in the dog, the dog does not require medication.
Rule4: The dog has a scheduled appointment in the morning or the dog has a scheduled appointment in the afternoon.

Rule5: Whenever the dog has a scheduled appointment in the afternoon and Dr. Smith is available as a veterinarian, if it is not the case that the dog shows symptoms of parvovirus implies parvovirus is diagnosed in the dog, then the dog does not require medication.
Rule6: If the facility has operating hours, then the facility is not closed.
Rule7: Provided that the facility has emergency hours, the facility is not closed.
Rule8: Whenever a receptionist is staffing the front desk, the medical team is ready.
Rule9: A receptionist is staffing the front desk or a technician is staffing the back office.
Rule10: Under the condition that a technician is staffing the back office, the facility has emergency hours.
Rule11: The veterinarian performs surgery or the veterinarian performs diagnosis.
Rule12: Under the condition that cage1 is a clean kennel, the dog has successful treatment.
Rule13: Either cage1 is a clean kennel or cage2 is a clean kennel.
Rule14: Whenever the waiting room has arranged furniture, the shelves have stocked supplies.
Rule15: The waiting room has arranged furniture or the treatment room has arranged furniture.

Rule16: If the treatment room has arranged furniture, then under the condition that it is false that cage2 is a clean kennel only if the dog has successful treatment, the dog and cat are separated animals.

Rule17: If the client has a confirmed appointment, then whenever the shelves have stocked supplies and it is not true that cage2 is a clean kennel only if the dog has successful treatment, the dog and cat are separated animals.
Rule18: Under the condition that the veterinarian performs diagnosis, either the veterinarian has authorization for the facility or the dog has successful treatment.
Rule19: If the credit card has processed payment, then the dog has successful treatment.
Rule20: Whenever cash has processed payment, the dog has successful treatment.

Rule21: Provided that the chart has updated medical records, if it is not the case that either the credit card has processed payment or cash has processed payment, then the policy has verified insurance.
Rule22: The chart has updated medical records or the chart has filed medical records.

Rule23: Whenever the dog has authorized discharge, if the chart has filed medical records and it is not true that either the credit card has processed payment or cash has processed payment, then the policy has verified insurance.
Rule24: The dog has completed treatment or the dog is under an observation period.
Rule25: Under the condition that the dog is under an observation period, the dog has authorized discharge.
Rule26: If a reminder is sent to the client, then a follow-up is scheduled for the dog.
Rule27: A reminder is sent to the client or no follow-up is needed for the dog.
Rule28: If no follow-up is needed for the dog, then whenever the dog has completed treatment, the dog has authorized discharge.
Rule29: If surgery is an emergency procedure, then surgery is an approved procedure.

Rule30: Provided that sterilization protocol is followed, if it is not the case that whenever it is false that the technician being trained staff implies that if a receptionist is staffing the front desk then the facility has operating hours, the technician needs certification, and it is not true that the technician is not a certified technician, then surgery is an emergency procedure.

Rule31: If isolation protocol is followed, then under the condition that it is not true that whenever it is false that the technician being trained staff implies that if a receptionist is staffing the front desk then the facility has operating hours, the technician needs certification, and it is not the case that the technician is not a certified technician, then surgery is an emergency procedure.
Rule32: Whenever the manager is an approved supervisor, sterilization protocol is followed.
Rule33: Provided that the director is an approved supervisor, isolation protocol is followed.
Rule34: If the compliance audit is passed, then either the manager is an approved supervisor or the director is an approved supervisor.
Rule35: The compliance audit is passed or the compliance audit is failed.
Rule36: Under the condition that the compliance audit is failed, either the manager is an approved supervisor or the director is an approved supervisor.
Rule37: If the owner has a conflict of interest, then the clinic is referred out.
Rule38: Provided that the owner has a conflict of interest, a second opinion is sought.
Rule39: Either the owner has a conflict of interest or if the dog has completed treatment, then the dog has authorized discharge.
Rule40: If a second opinion is sought, then the clinic is not referred out.
Rule41: Under the condition that the dog is sick, the dog is not healthy.
Rule42: Provided that the dog needs treatment, the dog is sick.
Rule43: Whenever it is not true that instruments being sterilized equipment implies that if the medical team is ready then the facility has operating hours, instruments are contaminated equipment.
Rule44: If it is false that instruments are sterilized equipment only if whenever the medical team is ready the facility has operating hours, then instruments are not contaminated equipment.
Rule45: Under the condition that it is false that cage2 is a clean kennel only if the dog has successful treatment, the dog and cat are not separated animals.

Rule46: Whenever it is not the case that the dog arriving at the clinic implies that if the veterinarian performs surgery then either the veterinarian has authorization for the facility or the dog has successful treatment, the dog is healthy.

Rule47: If it is not true that the dog arrives at the clinic implies that provided the veterinarian performs surgery, either the veterinarian has authorization for the facility or the dog has successful treatment, then the dog needs treatment.

Rule48: If it is false that the technician is trained staff only if whenever a receptionist is staffing the front desk the facility has operating hours, then the technician does not need certification.
Rule49: Under the condition that it is not true that the dog shows symptoms of parvovirus implies parvovirus is diagnosed in the dog, the dog requires medication.

Rule50: Provided that it is not the case that whenever it is false that the technician being trained staff implies that if a receptionist is staffing the front desk then the facility has operating hours, the technician needs certification, the technician is a certified technician.
Rule51: If the dog does not have successful treatment, then the facility is closed.
Rule52: Under the condition that the dog does not have successful treatment, the dog shows symptoms of parvovirus.
facts: Fact2: The client has a confirmed appointment.
Fact3: The dog arrives at the clinic.
Fact4: The technician is trained staff.
Fact5: It is not the case that the veterinarian has authorization for the facility.
Fact6: The policy does not have verified insurance.
Fact7: A follow-up is not scheduled for the dog.
Fact8: Surgery is not an approved procedure.
Fact9: Parvovirus is not diagnosed in the dog.
